lead_paragraph: Rick Porcello pitched seven innings to become the first 20-game winner in the majors, Hanley Ramirez hit a three-run homer and the Boston Red Sox increased their AL East lead to two games by routing the Toronto Blue Jays 13-3 on Friday night.

headline.print_headline: Porcello Gets 20th Win, Red Sox Rout Blue Jays 13-3
